CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 12, 1960, pg. A19, reads: "Westinghouse Gets Prize Picture - Ulysses Wall (center) presents Dr. Felton, principal of Westinghouse High School, with the picture the former won for his essay entitled 'Extrusion' in the science show on TV Channel 13 recently.  The picture, 'The Alchemists,' is one of the 10 like it which were awarded to high school students in the area.  Mr. Seate, the winner's science teacher, helps with the presentation.  Ulysses was the only boy in Pittsburgh to receive this award. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Westinghouse High School student Ulysses Wall holding "The Alchemist" picture with science teacher Mr. Seate and principal Paul Felton
